---
const canonical = 'https://1000namesofmakali.com/sources/';
const title = 'Sources and Editorial Notes | Adya Mahakali 1000 Names';
const description = 'Source notes, editorial approach, and correction path for the Adya Mahakali 1000 Names devotional reference.';
const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'WebPage',
      '@id': `${canonical}#webpage`,
      name: 'Sources and Editorial Notes',
      description,
      url: canonical,
      inLanguage: 'en',
      isPartOf: {
        '@id': 'https://1000namesofmakali.com/#website'
      },
      about: {
        '@type': 'Thing',
        name: 'Adya Mahakali Sahasranama'
      }
    },
    {
      '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
      '@id': `${canonical}#breadcrumb`,
      itemListElement: [
        {
          '@type': 'ListItem',
          position: 1,
          name: 'Home',
          item: 'https://1000namesofmakali.com/'
        },
        {
          '@type': 'ListItem',
          position: 2,
          name: 'Sources and Editorial Notes',
          item: canonical
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta name="robots" content="index,follow,max-image-preview:large,max-snippet:-1" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:url" content={canonical} />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://1000namesofmakali.com/MaaAdyaKali_5.webp" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://1000namesofmakali.com/MaaAdyaKali_5.webp" />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonical} />
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/plain" href="/llms.txt" title="LLMs text summary" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static-pages.css" />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)}></script>
  </head>
  <body class="names-static names-static--source">
    <main>
      <p class="page-kicker">Project notes</p>
      <h1>Sources and Editorial Notes</h1>

      <section class="hero-panel">
        <p class="intro">This page explains how the Adya Mahakali 1000 Names reference is presented, what public source material is acknowledged, and how corrections can be reported.</p>
        <nav class="page-nav" aria-label="Source notes navigation">
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/">Open the interactive reader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/names/">Browse the static names hub</a></li>
            <li><a href="/pdf/">Download the free PDF editions</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </section>

      <section class="source-notes" aria-labelledby="source-basis-heading">
        <h2 id="source-basis-heading">Source basis</h2>
        <p>This project compiles devotional source material and explanatory meaning notes for spiritual study, chanting support, and reference use.</p>
        <p>Primary public references used during compilation include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://sanskritdocuments.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer">SanskritDocuments.org</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>The site presents a reader-friendly English reference and does not claim to replace traditional instruction, lineage guidance, or primary manuscript study.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="source-notes" aria-labelledby="editorial-approach-heading">
        <h2 id="editorial-approach-heading">Editorial approach</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The names are organized into a searchable homepage reader and crawlable static range pages.</li>
          <li>Each entry includes a short English meaning and a longer explanatory note where available.</li>
          <li>Static range pages are intended for citation because their content is visible without JavaScript.</li>
          <li>Spelling and transliteration choices are kept consistent within the project where possible.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="source-notes" aria-labelledby="corrections-heading">
        <h2 id="corrections-heading">Corrections and attribution</h2>
        <p>If you notice a spelling, meaning, formatting, attribution, or source issue, please report it through the open-source repository so the correction can be reviewed clearly.</p>
        <p>When citing this site, please attribute the material to <strong>Adya Mahakali 1000 Names</strong> and link to the relevant canonical page, such as the <a href="/names/">static names hub</a> or a specific name-range page.</p>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/09ashishkapoor/1000namesofmaadya" rel="noopener noreferrer">View the open-source repository</a></p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
